  "prompt": "The Last Man on Earth (TV series): Where did all the dead bodies go on The Last Man on Earth?",
  "response": "In the TV series \"The Last Man on Earth,\" most of the world's population is wiped out by a virus. However, the show doesn't explicitly address where all the dead bodies have gone. The series focuses more on the comedic and dramatic aspects of Phil Miller's life and the interactions with other survivors rather than the logistical details of dealing with deceased people. It's meant to be a lighthearted, post-apocalyptic comedy, so certain practical or somber elements, like handling the aftermath of the virus in terms of bodies, are intentionally left unexplored to maintain the tone of the show.",
